The '''Mercedes-Benz EQS (V297)''' is a [[Battery electric vehicle|battery electric]] [[full-size car|full-size]] [[luxury vehicle|luxury liftback]] produced by German automobile manufacturer [[Mercedes-Benz Group]]. It was released in September 2021 in Germany and the fourth quarter of the year in the US.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Aquilina|first=John|date=10 August 2021|title=Mercedes EQS launches for €106,374|url=https://www.electrive.com/2021/08/10/mercedes-eqs-launches-for-e106374/|url-status=live|website=electrive.com|language=en-US}}</ref> It is part of the [[Mercedes-EQ|Mercedes-Benz EQ]] family.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.autoexpress.co.uk/mercedes/eq/104513/mercedes-to-launch-10-all-electric-models-by-2022|title=Mercedes to launch 10 all-electric models by 2022|work=Auto Express|access-date=7 September 2018|language=en}}</ref>

== Presentation ==
[[File:Mercedes-Benz Vision EQS at IAA 2019 IMG 0753.jpg|thumb|left|Mercedes-Benz Vision EQS Concept at IAA 2019]]
The EQS was presented at the [[International Motor Show Germany#2019|International Motor Show Germany in 2019]] as the Mercedes-Benz Vision EQS and foreshadows the future Mercedes-Benz series luxury electric sedan announced for 2021. The production model debuted on 15 April 2021.

{{clear left}}

== Technical details ==
[[File:Mercedes-Benz V297 Classic-Days 2022 DSC 0070.jpg|left|thumb|Rear view]]
[[File:Mercedes-AMG V297 IAA 2021 1X7A0040.jpg|thumb|left|Mercedes-AMG EQS 53 4MATIC+]]

The EQS is the first EQ model that is based on the technical platform specific to the electric models, called the MEA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/new-cars/mercedes-benz-launch-ultra-luxurious-eq-s-electric-saloon-2020|title=Mercedes-Benz to launch ultra-luxurious EQ S electric saloon in 2020|work=Autocar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/industry/mercedes-eq-s-be-flagship-%C2%A39bn-electric-model-blitz|title=Mercedes EQ S to be flagship in £9bn electric model blitz &#124; Autocar|website=www.autocar.co.uk}}</ref> The car's [[Automobile drag coefficient|drag coefficient]] is as low as 0.20, making it the most aerodynamic car in production at the time of its introduction.<ref>[https://www.cnet.com/roadshow/news/2022-mercedes-benz-eqs-ev-most-aerodynamic-car/ The electric Mercedes EQS is the world's most aerodynamic production car] Cnet.com / 15 April 2021</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Finally: say hello to the Mercedes EQS !|url=https://www.topgear.com/car-news/electric/finally-say-hello-mercedes-eqs | date=15 April 2021|publication-date=}}</ref>

The car is powered by a water-cooled [[permanent magnet motor|permanent magnet synchronous motor]] from Valeo Siemens in the EQS 450+ model, and by two of these motors in the EQS 580 4MATIC model. The torque is sent from the motor(s) to the wheels through a single-speed reduction gearbox. In the single-motor EQS 450+ model, the motor has a rated power of {{convert|245|kW|abbr=on}}, and a braking power of {{convert|186|kW|abbr=on}}, allowing a deceleration of 5&nbsp;m·s<sup>−2</sup>. German motor journalist [[Alexander Bloch]] from [[auto motor und sport]] found the energy consumption to be 150…160&nbsp;W·h/km at {{convert|130|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}, and the average energy consumption to be 158&nbsp;W·h/km. With the 107.8&nbsp;kW·h secondary cell, the car has a range of more than 638&nbsp;km. The average recharging power is 163&nbsp;kW with a peak of >200&nbsp;kW, allowing the car to reach a 79 % state of charge in about half an hour.<ref>Patrick Lang: ''[https://www.auto-motor-und-sport.de/elektroauto/bloch-erklaert-mercedes-eqs-450plus-elektroauto-reichweite/ Das wirklich beste Elektroauto der Welt!]'' in auto motor und sport, 27 June 2021, retrieved 15 July 2021 (in German)</ref>

The Mercedes-AMG EQS 53 4Matic+ was presented at the Munich Motor Show in September 2021 and is the first all-electric AMG car. It has two electric motors producing {{convert|560|kW|0|abbr=on}} of power and delivering {{convert|1,020|Nm|0|abbr=on}} of torque. Its handling characteristics as well as its cooling system have been upgraded to match the motors' higher power output.<ref>[https://paultan.org/2021/09/06/mercedes-amg-eqs53-4matic-revealed/ Mercedes-AMG EQS53 4Matic+ revealed – brand’s first performance EV receives up to 761 PS and 1,020 Nm] Gerard Lye / 6 September 2021</ref>

== Equipment ==
The car comes with [[Steering#Four-wheel steering|rear-wheel steering]], [[Over-the-air-Update|over-the-air updates]], [[Inductive charging|wireless phone charging]], 360-degree camera system, keyless entry and can optionally be equipped with seats with massage, [[augmented reality]] [[head-up display]], automatically opening and closing doors, integrated toll payment system, gesture controls, [[HEPA|HEPA air filter]], heat, noise and infrared rays insulated glass and heated windshield.<ref name=":2" />

===MBUX Hyperscreen===
[[File:Mercedes-AMG V297 IAA 2021 1X7A0184.jpg|thumb|left|Interior]]
The high-end versions of Mercedes-Benz EQS feature two separate OLED screens and an LCD instrument cluster that covers nearly the full extension of the dashboard.<ref>{{Cite web|date=7 January 2021|title=The Mercedes EQS has this vast all-digital dashboard|url=https://www.topgear.com/car-news/electric/mercedes-eqs-has-vast-all-digital-dashboard|access-date=10 January 2021|website=Top Gear|language=en}}</ref> The whole infotainment system is powered by eight CPU cores and 24-gigabytes of RAM.<ref>{{Cite web|date=7 January 2021|title=Mercedes-Benz MBUX Hyperscreen is a vast digital dash for the 2022 EQS electric sedan|url=https://www.slashgear.com/mercedes-benz-mbux-hyperscreen-is-a-vast-digital-dash-for-the-2022-eqs-electric-sedan-07653860/|access-date=10 January 2021|website=SlashGear|language=en-US}}</ref> The multi-purpose digital dashboard has been well received by consumers.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Golson|first=Daniel|title=Mercedes-Benz design chief Gorden Wagener on the EQS' Hyperscreen: 'Bigger the better'|url=https://www.cnet.com/roadshow/news/mercedes-benz-design-chief-gorden-wagener-on-the-eqs-hyperscreen-bigger-the-better/|access-date=10 January 2021|website=Roadshow|language=en}}</ref>

===Safety and automated features===
The car has several safety and automated features: [[adaptive cruise control]], [[lane centering]], automatic lane changing, [[Collision avoidance system|automated emergency braking]], avoidance assist (for pedestrians and bicycles), [[Active Blind Spot Assist|blind spot monitoring]] including rear seat exit warning, cross-traffic alert, traffic-sign recognition, [[Automatic parking|automatic parking assist]], [[adaptive headlights]].<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnet.com/roadshow/features/2022-mercedes-benz-eqs-ev-electric-sedan-debut-specs-details/|title=2022 Mercedes-Benz EQS electric sedan: Design, specs and all the details|first=Daniel|last=Golson|website=Roadshow}}</ref>

The car can optionally be fit with a [[Self-driving car#Levels of driving automation|level 3 autonomous driving]] feature named ''Drive Pilot'' allowing the driver to take his hands off the wheel and his eyes off the road in heavy traffic up to a {{convert|60|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}} speed on {{convert|13,191|km}} of [[Autobahn|German motorways]]. The system is a World first and works by using [[Lidar|LiDAR]], cameras, microphones and various sensors. It is planned to also become available to other countries.<ref>{{Cite web|date=10 December 2021|title=Mercedes : première validation pour une voiture autonome|url=https://www.autojournal.fr/mercedes/mercedes-premiere-validation-pour-une-voiture-autonome-279142.html|url-status=live|website=Auto Journal|language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Mercedes Gets International Approval For Level 3 Autonomous Tech |url=https://www.motor1.com/news/553833/mercedes-benz-level-3-approval/ |access-date=19 May 2022 |website=Motor1.com |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Group |first=Mercedes-Benz |date=6 April 2022 |title=Mercedes-Benz – the front runner in automated driving and safety technologies |url=https://group.mercedes-benz.com/innovation/case/autonomous/drive-pilot-2.html |access-date=19 May 2022 |website=Mercedes-Benz Group |language=en}}</ref> The car is the first that can be fit a [[Self-driving car#Levels of driving automation|level 4]] automated valet parking system named ''Intelligent Park Pilot''.<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Dieter |date=23 July 2019 |title=Mercedes is first OEM to offer level 4 automated valet parking |url=https://www.globalfleet.com/fr/autonomous/europe/features/mercedes-first-oem-offer-level-4-automated-valet-parking |access-date=19 May 2022 |website=Global Fleet |language=en}}</ref>

